⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Billy Bob
node VBL · VBL · ⟦Billy Bob:VBL:202198⟧

WHO   — Billy Bob — the lineman sent back in
WHAT  — The body that breaks: the loyal big man whose rung-bell head became, in hindsight, the most serious thing in the film.
WHERE — VBL · Varsity Blues (1999)  Framework inputs: Varsity Blues (1999, dir. Brian Robbins, MTV Films/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the film's real subject — the cost to young bodies — needs a face, and his is it.
HOW   — By taking the shots, going back in concussed, and scoring the touchdown he can barely remember.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Coach says I'm fine, so they shoot me up and send me back in. I scored the winning play — I just can't remember it.

